>Description:
Delete is mapped to backspace by default in Linux distributions. In almost no other text editing software is this the case. Although done on purpose, it is infuriating, and this is compounded by the obscure menus you have to go through in order to change this binding.
>How-To-Repeat:
Start DrScheme in Linux. Press delete.
